Input: Create a rule that deletes horizontal lines.
Output:

Here we want to delete horizontal lines so we will put a horizontal line on the left side.

Input: Create a rule that deletes all green dots in the image.
Output:
Normally these dots are used as markers during rule application but we need to delete them at the end of all the steps. To do this we will have a rule that turns all the green dots into nothing.
We will make the left side of the rule, the green dot in question and the right side of the rule nothing.
